<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 28 at 1:31AM EDT  by NWS Columbia</headline>
<description>...Increased Fire Danger Today and Thursday...
Strong Canadian surface high pressure will build SE into the Upper
Midwest and Great Lakes region today through Thursday, and direct
dry air into our region. The surface pressure gradient, between
the high well to our north and Tropical Cyclone Ian to our south,
will result in gradually increasing wind speeds from the NE.
The current forecast indicates minimum RH values this afternoon
dropping to around 25 percent, with peak wind gusts from the NE
around 20 mph. On Thursday, slightly lower temperatures will lead
to higher RH values, but winds are expected to increase as Ian
moves closer. Current forecast indicates minimum afternoon RH
values Thursday around 30 to 35 percent, with peak wind gusts
from the NE around 30 mph.
This will lead to increased fire danger concerns.</description>
